Seems like `buildah` is aware that there's a shell change, but isn't utilising it.

I've tracked down the issue to the `if` condition in [StageExecutor.Run](https://github.com/containers/buildah/blob/master/imagebuildah/build.go#L591). I've managed to resolve the issue by modifying the code in the following way:
```go
	if run.Shell {
		if len(config.Shell) > 0 && s.builder.Format == buildah.Dockerv2ImageManifest {
			args = append(config.Shell, args...)
		} else {
			args = append([]string{"/bin/sh", "-c"}, args...)
		}
	}
```
This functionality is only enabled when `--format=docker` is specified. In my tests this seems to have worked both when `SHELL` was specified and omitted (with Docker format both enabled and disabled). Should I create PR for this?
